sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212021
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The strongest Anderson Family Promoter, J23100, with TALe binding site 2 controls the expression of GFP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amy Soon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212020
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: TALe Binding Site 2, which corresponds to TAL 8 in front of a strong RBS, GFP with an LVA tag, and a double terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amy Soon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212019
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: GFP+LVA tag + B0015 with BsaI site removed and Golden Gate Assembly site used in our construction.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amy Soon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212018
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: B0015 terminator with overhang used in our Golden Gate Assembly.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amy Soon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: K145015 with LVA tag fixed for Golden Gate compatibility through site directed mutagenesis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Aura Ferreiro

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: TALe Binding Site 2 (specific to TAL repressor 2)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: DNA binding sequence for transcriptional activator like (TAL) repressor 2 (part BBa_K1212006). High binding affinity.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Aura Ferreiro
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Synthetic. Assembled in the Segal Lab at UC Davis GBSF. See: 'Quantitative Analysis of TALE-DNA Interactions Suggests Polarity Effects' by Meckler et al., submitted to Nucleic Acids Research for review.
